Its been a month of back-to-back football action in Cameroon, where Senegal were crowned champions for the first time, after beating Egypt 4-2 on penalties on Sunday night at the Olembe Stadium in Yaounde. Senegal coach, Aliou Cisse, upon his teamâ€™s victory, praised his team for winning the title on Cameroonian soil, saying Cameron is a land of soccer, thus winning the title there was a beautiful sign. Cisse further praised his team for making history, beating seven-time champions, Egypt. The win comes on the back of comments on Friday by team captain, Sadio Mane, who said they will be playing to win the Afcon for Cisse, for his contribution to Senegalese football. --ChannelAfrica--